                <head>
                    <supplied resp="editorial">Title and caption</supplied></head>
                <p>THE DEADLY UPAS TREE OF WALL STREET.</p>
                <p>"This tree.....was said to be so exceedingly poisonous that no one could even
                    approach it without certain death."-<hi rendition="#italics">Zell's
                        Encyclop√¶dia</hi></p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Artist" n="2">
                <head>
                    <supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000000379">Joseph Ferdinand Keppler</persName> </supplied></head>
                <p>J. KEPPLER</p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Cornell" n="3">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000003572">Alonzo Cornell</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>BLIND POOL CORNELL.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Stockholder" n="4">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Stockholder</supplied></head>
                <p>STOCKHOLDER.</p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Friday" n="5">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000000941">Ulysses S. Grant</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>BLACK FRIDAY.<note n="1" type="editorial">On September 24, 1869, or Black Friday, Jim Fisk and Jay Gould's financial schemes led to the collapse of the US gold market.  Grant's presidency was tarnished by the scandal because of his association with Gould and Fisk.</note></p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Stockholder_2" n="6">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial">Stockholder</supplied></head>
                <p>STOCK HOLDER E.R.R <note n="2" type="editorial">Next to the label Stockholder lies the body of woman.</note></p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#West" n="7">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000003571">Theodoric Westbrook</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>WESTBRO<note n="3" type="editorial">Theodoric Westbrook is slumped over a row of buildings and wears a hat with his name inscribed on it.  Westbrook was a lawyer, congressman from New York, and NY State Supreme Court Justice.  He was suspected of supporting Gould in his effort to acquire the Manhattan Elevated Railroad.</note></p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Reid" n="8">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000003377">Whitelaw Reid</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>WHITELAW REID.<note n="4" type="editorial">Whitelaw Reid is lying on the ground with his arms outstretched.  Reid was a politician, journalist and editor of the <hi rendition="#italics"><orgName key="ENT.000003329">New York Tribune</orgName></hi>.</note></p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Fisk" n="9">
                <head><supplied resp="editorial"><persName key="ENT.000003558">Jim Fisk</persName></supplied></head>
                <p>JIM FISK.<note n="5" type="editorial" >Below the large tree, there is a skull labeled "Jim Fisk".  Jim Fisk was Jay Gould's business partner.  He was murdered in 1872 by his ex-lover's boyfriend.</note></p>
            </div>

            <div type="image_transcription" facs="#Congress" n="10">
